Package: rcomplex
Title: Comparative Co-Expression Network Analysis Across Species
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Martin", "Paliocha", , "martin.paliocha@nmbu.no", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Compares gene co-expression networks across species by mapping
    orthologous genes, building co-expression networks independently per species,
    then testing conservation at gene, module, and clique levels. Includes
    hypergeometric and permutation-based neighborhood tests, multi-resolution
    consensus module detection (Leiden / Infomap / SBM), clique detection via
    Bron-Kerbosch decomposition with leave-k-out jackknife stability analysis,
    and HOG conservation classification.
    Based on Netotea et al. (2014) <doi:10.1186/1471-2164-15-106>.
